Pre-Game Insights: Cameroon were held to a 1-1 draw by Angola in the 2026 FIFA World Cup qualifiers.
Namibia were outclassed and outplayed by Angola in the 2024 COSAFA Cup final, suffering a 5-0 loss.
Cameroon have picked up two wins and two draws in their four World Cup qualifying matches to sit top of Group D.
Namibia have claimed two wins and two draws from their four matches in Group H to collect eight points and sit second in the table.
Cameroon's Vincent Aboubakar is currently third in the nation's all-time scoring chart with 39 goals in 102 caps.
Namibia's Edmar Kamatuka, Bethuel Muzeu, and Erastus Kulula started the game against Angola last time out and should lead the Brave Warriors' attack.
